  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Financial Institution Obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal compliance programs\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n\n6. Typical Predicate Offenses\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Terrorist financing\n- Organized crime\n\n7. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal imprisonment\n- Professional license revocation\n- Organizational sanctions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes globally.",
